Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring @butter{2%tbsp} to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Using a heavy-bottomed pan or #rolling pin{}, crush @walnuts{1/2%ounce} in their bag until finely ground. In a #small bowl{}, combine walnuts, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and place in 1 #oven-ready aluminum tray{}. (For 4 servings, divide chicken between 2 trays.) Season chicken all over with half the @fry seasoning{2%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

Evenly spread tops of chicken with half the @honey Dijon dressing{1.5%ounce} (save the rest for serving). Mound coated sides with panko mixture, pressing to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary; place in remaining #oven-ready aluminum tray{}. Toss with a drizzle of olive oil and season with salt and pepper; drizzle with @water{2%tbsp}. (For 4 servings, divide broccoli between remaining trays. Use 2 TBSP water for each tray.) Cover tray tightly with #foil{}.

Roast chicken on top rack and broccoli on middle rack until chicken is browned and cooked through and broccoli is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> If broccoli is done before chicken, remove from oven and continue roasting chicken.

While chicken and broccoli roast, halve @ciabatta bread{1}.

In a second #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @butter{2%tbsp}(softened) and half the remaining @fry seasoning{1%tbsp} (use the rest as you like). Season with salt and pepper.

> If butter is not yet softened, microwave for 5-10 seconds before mixing with the seasoning.

Spread seasoned butter onto cut sides of ciabatta and evenly sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}.

When chicken has 5 minutes left, carefully place ciabatta cut sides up directly on oven rack (or use a #baking sheet{}). Bake until bread is toasted and cheese melts, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Halve ciabatta on a diagonal; divide between plates along with chicken and broccoli. Serve with remaining Honey Dijon Dressing on the side for dipping.